<Rating>5< /Rating>< review>
This place has delicious food. Perfect place to eat if you are looking to eat healthy and on the go. They have excellent agua frescas, the fruit cups are packed with bomb fruit. I think that adding avocado to your ceviche orders is a must, it makes a huge difference. I discovered this gem a few weeks ago and I got my family hooked. I love that the Kansas Location had a drive threw, the only thing that sucks is that it doesn't have the variety of ice cream flavors that the store on Roselle has, they only serve vanilla...wack...but over all this place is bomb, clean and the customer service is also great.< /review>

<Rate>1</Rate>< review>
This dog park presents it‚Äôs self as well kept and in good shape. But honestly this park is terrible, the dirt with pebbles every where is horrible for dogs as it can rip up their pause which can cause severe damage. As well the water fountain in the large dog area does not work at all! And to top that there was glass shards all throughout the back side of the big dog area. My dog only played for 15 minutes before he started limping from the pebbles hurting his paws. Will not be going back. If anyone else is dissatisfied I suggest going to the Redhawk dog park by Temecula park way. It has grass and water fountains that work. As well they keep up on the maintenance.</review>

<Review>I recently bought a used Ninja 250r and it quickly got a flat tire. I had it towed to Berkeley Performance Motorcycle for new tires; since it was in the shop anyway, I went ahead and requested a carb clean because it had some issues starting up and would stumble quite a bit after it warmed up -- I just suspected that it was a carb-related issue. Within the next couple business days, Carra contacted me via phone and text to let me know that the tires were put on and that the carb was actually in good condition and needed no work. It turned out that the issue was attributable to some leftover bad gas (an oversight on my part). Carra further informed me of a couple other minor issues that she could take care of, but didn't do anything without my permission. <rating>5</rating>< Review>
Move in; wonderful experience! Staff and especially the manager; excellent customer service, pleasant and extremely accommodating. The staff and the manager ensured that we were happy with our apartment and more than once checked up on us to ensure we were settled in and happy. The maintenance staff are also extremely professional and accommodating; ensuring the grounds are well kept and asked upon move in if our apartment required any maintenance request. The apartment chosen for us is beautiful; hardwood floors throughout most of the apartment, fireplace, laundry room; and washing and machine and dryer hook ups; and our patio face a beautiful pond with ducks, turtles and beautiful trees. Every morning and evening, my husband and I look forward to sitting on our patio and enjoying the nature and the view. The apartment complex is extremely quite at night and during the day, full of family life. I highly recommend The Terracina Apartment Homes for individuals who are considering apartment living.</Review>

I know this complex is under new ownership/management but to charge what you did when it was so outdated is a darn shame. Everything should be replaced in this apartment from top to bottom.

<Rate>2</Rate>< review>
We gave our notice to vacate. This is not because of our unhappiness, but because we bought a house so it was time to vacate.

Firstly, I want to express that giving your tenants a paper notice taped to your door shouldn't be the first thing of how I believe good customer service should be handled. Should something as serious as the need to understand if we were staying or going arise, a phone call to set up a meeting would have been the first step. If you cannot reach us by phone/email then proceed to give us a written letter.

When we (my wife and I) went to the office to sign our 30-day notice, we felt that we were being handled very unprofessionally. They were not sure who could help us, they gave us an incorrect estimated total (for our closing cost - had to call to reconfirm what the total was), and to top it off, the attire of the employee made us feel very uncomfortable. She had to hold her blouse when reviewing our paperwork (an unsightly experience).

The very next day, another staff member contacted me via phone and asked if my wife and I was to stay or go. I informed her that I came in the day before and let the office know. She assumed that I signed papers to extend our stay but then I clarified and said that my wife and I signed the notice to vacate. She then commented how she was not notified and bid me adieu.

Secondly, I noticed that there are days on end that the gate is open. If this is to be a gated community, then why is this repeatedly happening? The gates should always be well maintained or monitored. If it was simply a day that the gate stayed open, then I could understand, but I went a week long without having to click my gate (and this is not because a car just went through). If you're seeking for a temporary gated community, then you're in for a treat.

Thirdly, maintenance - I still stand by them being cordial and responding in a timely manner. I get it. There are a lot of units. But, the problem I have and I am not sure if it pertains to maintenance is how the lawn, edges, and bushes have been maintained. There were weeks where the complex looked awful (leaves everywhere, cut grass patches laid about, and hours later the person who was the blow the leftover cut grass would plummet these things onto parked cars - my car needed to be washed every other day; it got rather dusty - car port didn't help).

Fourthly, if you are expecting quiet nights and mornings, think again. There are trucks that keep on unloading over behind the Ralphs, people who speed in the parking lots (rev up their motorcycles or sports cars), the Tae Kwon Do class kids yelling their weekly routines - this noise ricochets and you can do nothing about it.

Lastly, for the price you pay for a place like this, you would think the grounds would be better maintained, and security clearly around to keep the scary characters away. In addition to the price you pay, you would think that you would have cordial neighbors (ones that say hi with a smile, or ones that keep their noise level down after 10PM or before 8AM).

I was close to giving this a 3-star review, but as I wrote, my review calls to be left at a 2-star. Thanks for the year here - I wish we were better served for our tenure.<//review>

< Review>
Overall, i like this place. i live on the archibald side and it is very quiet. Neighbors are friendly, staff is helpful (when you can get the office to answer the phone), apartment is nice looking (although it was not repainted before we moved in. lots of scratches and black marks on walls and ceiling), and its affordable. With my experience, every time i have called for maintenance, it has gotten fixed same day.

My only complaints are the gate does break often and stay open till fixed. i've never seen it broken for more than two days. My upstairs neighbors stomp the yard up there till about 1:30 in the morning. They are constantly walking back and forth up there when they are home. Not a problem until it gets past 10pm and my child still cant fall asleep because of their heavy foot. and bonus, we get to hear every time they are having their affectionate time. which is any time of the day. (of course; not really management problem, but its still disturbing)

Other than that, i like this place. Haven't had any issues with the staff and everyone there is very friendly. i'm nervous to see how the move out is going to be if we do not renew. i keep hearing horror stories about it. but i did my research and know the laws. so hopefully, it comes out easy.

UPDATE: We gave our notice and moved out at the beginning of May 2016. The new management that purchased the complex are trying to claim that we made so many horrible scratches to the walls and we have to pay for repaint.

I called on 06/03, Friday, Stating that we should not have to pay for repaint as the previous tenants made those scratches and the place was not repainted for our move in. I took pictures and have a ton of notes on the back of the initial move in inspection sheet, (Which i have copies of). The good for nothing lady who usually answers the phone told me that she will call me no later than Tuesday, 06/07. It is now 06/13 and i had to call her to see what the problem is. I definitely miss the old company MG Properties with Margaret, who was AMAZING!  I refuse to pay for repaint! we were only there for 6 months or so and did not make those scratches. I will be contacting corporate and maybe a lawyer at that.

I am only giving one star because i cannot give zero and the new management company has horrible customer service! if it were MG Properties, i would keep the 4 stars. Unfortunately, this new company is horrid and i would not recommend this place to anyone.

< username>

< Time>
1434007126927<//Time>
< rating>
4< /rating>
< Text>
Becker's Bakery may not have the selection that some other bakeries in the area boast, but what they do, they do REALLY WELL. The cronuts are large, rich, and have an amazing flaky and moist texture. The donuts are yeasty, sweet, and light as air. I didn't get a chance to sample one of their many cupcakes, but the cookies were huge and chewy.

In the area cronut wars, I thought Beckers was far superior to Torrance Bakery (though Torrance's cookies come out on top for me). All in all, a must stop if you are around the Manhattan Beach area and looking for a treat!<//Text>

<Review>Wonderful chocolate chip cookies. As big as my face!</Review><Response>None< /Response><Pictures>None</Pictures></record></dataset><record>
< Text>
I used to say I'm not into cupcakes, but thanks to Yelp (with an expanding waistline to prove it), I am very much a cupcake fiend.  If I find out about a place that is known for their cupcakes, I AM THERE.   I actually found out AFTER-the-fact that this was a Cupcake Wars winner, and as much as I watch that show, I don't recall seeing them.  When you walk into this small storefront, you are hit with a bizillion cupcakes staring you in the face, with about 20 different flavors to choose from.  While we didn't get one of each, we came close.  We did opt for the mini size (so we could justify the multitude of flavors we wanted), but I have to say, the ONLY ones I cared for.......and that had any appreciable flavor recognition to what their names were.....were the chocolate raspberry mousse, the tres leches spicy mango (my favorite), and the honey bourbon (all of which were under their "specialty" cupcakes).  Honestly, everything else was just average.  Nothing bad.......just average.  They also sell macarons, but we didn't try any< /Text>
< user_name>
Whiy LLackie<//user_name>
< Pictures>
None< /Pictures>

<Name>Frank Yar< /Name><Text>Update:

My appointment was at 9:00 AM and I showed up at 10:30 am, EXTREMELY LATE. When I asked him how long it would take, they said. ‚ÄúI do not know‚Äù. I figured it would take 2-3 maybe 4 hours to complete an hour job and decided to stay in Fresno (since home was an hour away and I had no ride).

It was my fault to assume that they would finish the job within a reasonable amount of time. If they would have told me, ‚Äúwe won't get to your car until the end of the day‚Äù or ‚Äúplease make an appointment for another day‚Äù, then I could have prepared myself. In this case, ended up stuck in Fresno for 7 hours.

I still stand by my statement of lack of communication. In this situation, from both of us. I should have told them I was from out of town and had to way back home and they should have clarified my options and the situation. By the time they were done, I had a clear, calm head and I was happy with my purchase. From a scale of 1 to 5, five being best, I give the product a 5 star and customer service a 1.

The cashier guy seemed friendlier and the price seems reasonable, so I will try again for my truck.</Text>< Time>

<text>Outstanding for the price. Is it PF Changs? No. It is, however, surprisingly good Chinese take-away for like $7 a person. If that weren't enough, consider that each 3-item combo could serve as two meals if you stretch it. Will you stretch it? Probably not‚Äîit's darn tasty. My go-to order is the orange chicken, broccoli beef, and fried rice. Among other good options are the breaded, garlicky fish filets and chicken wings, teriyaki chicken, egg rolls, and pork ribs. It certainly ain't fancy, and those with a refined palate may not deem it worth eating no matter how low the price.
